ğŸ‘‰ï¸ pesudo-elements w.r.t inputs :

Pseudo-elements like ::before and ::after are typically used with container elements that have content. 
However, input elements are self-closing and cannot have child elements.
If you want to add additional elements or visuals to the input field, you can wrap the input element inside 
a container element and apply the pseudo-element styles to the containe

